    info: '<color="blue">Beetles</color> are a part of the largest order, <color="blue">Coleoptera</color>.
      The life cycle of a beetle starts with an <color="blue">egg</color> stage.
      Once hacthed, the <color="blue">larva</color> stage begins. The <color="blue">larva</color>
      will eat and grow turning into a <color="blue">pupa</color> where they will
      be immobile, typically during the winter months. In the spring, the <color="blue">adult</color>
      beetle will emerge and continue the cycle by feeding, mating, and laying eggs.


      Source:
